    <para id="id2263081"><emphasis effect="bold">Circle Criterion and Power Factor.</emphasis> Our study of the impedance
<m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mrow><m:mi>Z</m:mi><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mi>ν</m:mi><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math> and the function <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mstyle scriptlevel="0" displaystyle="true"><m:mrow><m:mi>H</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mi>ν</m:mi><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mrow><m:mi>Z</m:mi><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mi>ν</m:mi><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mfrac></m:mrow></m:mstyle></m:math> brings insight into the resonance of an
<emphasis effect="italics">RLC</emphasis> circuit and illustrates the ffequency selectivity of the circuit. But there
is more that we can do to illuminate the behavior of the circuit.</para>
    <equation id="eip-526"><m:math overflow="scroll">
        <m:mstyle scriptlevel="0" displaystyle="true">
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mi>V</m:mi>
            <m:mo>=</m:mo>
            <m:mi>R</m:mi>
            <m:mi>I</m:mi>
            <m:mo>+</m:mo>
            <m:mi>j</m:mi>
            <m:mo>(</m:mo>
            <m:mi>ω</m:mi>
            <m:mi>L</m:mi>
            <m:mo>-</m:mo>
            <m:mfrac>
              <m:mn>1</m:mn>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mi>ω</m:mi>
                <m:mi>C</m:mi>
              </m:mrow>
            </m:mfrac>
            <m:mo>)</m:mo>
            <m:mi>I</m:mi>
            <m:mo>.</m:mo>
          </m:mrow>
        </m:mstyle>
      </m:math>
    </equation>
    
